Review_Text: Even though the series appeals to a lot of teenagers, I was a teenager when I started watching it, but I continued until the end. It was sad.
What a fitting ending to a show that has brought good people into my real life, made giving back so much fun, & helped me find a place my weird fits. ðŸ’™ðŸ’™

The last seasons, especially the 15th, might not have been so good, but you kept us company so many years now that I can't complain about anything. The last episode of 15th season was so emotionally intense that for the first time I cried watching a film or series. Thank you for those amazing years lads!!

After 15 years, the cast and crew look back at the most memorable moments. Classic episodes, character introductions, unforgettable props, and the big story lines. No road lasts forever. This has everything to prepare you for the series finale.
What a great tribute. I will always be a true fan and keep watching and enjoying.
I was expecting proper interviews and in depth chats.But really this was a clip show with a bit of a chat in between.Should have been soo much more.

Ah yes, the writers, producers and others talk about the legacy of h*mophobia and m*sogyny.
15 years thrown down the drain, never to be seen again.
What's left, you ask?
Sam's party city wig is thriving, I hear!
Thank you cast members, Dabbs and the other guy? Not so much.
I just don't understand why they would do something so bad
